Package: interdep
Title: Tools for Cross-Sectional and Intensive Longitudinal Dyadic Data
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Pascal", "Küng", , "kueng.pascal@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Helps researchers prepare cross-sectional and intensive
    longitudinal dyadic data for statistical models. The package supports common
    dyadic designs with one kind of dyad, while also handling studies that
    combine different kinds of dyads, such as female-male, female-female, and
    male-male couples. It validates long-format dyadic data and creates the
    role, composition, and centering variables needed for multilevel models,
    including generalized multilevel models. Prepared data can be used to
    estimate dyadic models, including generalized intensive longitudinal
    actor-partner interdependence models with multiple dyad types in a single
    model.
